New Records: Spencer Strider achieved his major league-leading 17th win.
The Atlanta Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title.
The Braves' division title was their record 26th, two more than the Los Angeles Dodgers and New York Yankees.
The Braves are tied for most players with 35 homers in a season on one team in MLB history.
Key Match Events: Spencer Strider allowed one run and four hits in seven innings, striking out nine.
Austin Riley hit a two-run homer in the first inning.
Kirby Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game.
Kevin Pillar added an RBI double in the fourth inning.
Cristopher Sánchez struck out a career-best 10 in 7 1/3 innings.
Post-Match Reflections: Braves manager Brian Snitker said, 'We’ve checked one box.'
Phillies manager Rob Thomson said it would be a 'pleasant surprise' if injured first baseman Rhys Hoskins was able to return in the postseason.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched the NL East title on the same Citizens Bank Park field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series.
Ronald Acuña Jr. responded to booing fans by raising both arms and signaling with his hands to bring it on.
